HEADWORD: autotomy
<hw>autotomy</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>spontaneous removal or
casting off of a body part (as the tail of a lizard or claw or a
lobster) especially when the organism is injured or under
attack.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

